text: Roslina Bakar (born 22 August 1973) is a Malaysian sport shooter. Bakar competed at the Commonwealth Games in 1998 where she won a bronze medal in the 50m rifle three position event and at the 2002 Games where she won another bronze medal in the same event. ==References== Category:1973 births Category:Living people Category: Malaysian female sport shooters Category:Shooters at the 1998 Commonwealth Games Category:Shooters at the 2002 Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for Malaysia Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in shooting
